.ul
The man alone
.sp
Aragon
.sp 2
The man alone: a stair that goes
Nowhere for anyone. All the gates
Of the palaces remain
Inhuman to his single state.
.sp 2
The man alone has crooked limbs,
One eye, a life which does not count;
Elsewhere is his only pillow;
His sleep a girl of easy virtue.
.sp 2
The man alone: fingers of air;
Whatever he's given turns to ash;
When he takes it, even pleasure
Is, so he discovers, dust.
.sp 2
The man alone: he has no face;
Like window glass, he takes the rain;
The tears one sees upon him are
What the countryside has wept.
.sp 2
He's a letter gone astray.
Did he carry a wrong address?
To whom did it say 'tenderly'?
Whose hands should have torn it open?
